theorem
  for a,b being R_eal holds (a = -infty & b = +infty &
  (A = ].a,b.[ or A = [.a,b.] or A = [.a,b.[ or A = ].a,b.]))
  implies diameter(A) = +infty
proof
  let a,b be R_eal;
  assume
A1: a = -infty & b = +infty &
  (A = ].a,b.[ or A = [.a,b.] or A = [.a,b.[ or A = ].a,b.]);
B: sup A = +infty & inf A = -infty by A1,XXREAL_2:25,26,27,28,29,30,31,32;
  then A is non empty by XXREAL_2:40;
  then diameter(A) = b - a by Def10,A1,B
    .= +infty by A1,SUPINF_2:6;
  hence thesis;
end;

